      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/51/1042",
      "text": [
        " «لاَ يَقْضِي اَلصَّوْمَ وَ لاَ اَلصَّلاَةَ وَ كُلُّ مَا غَلَبَ اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ فَاللَّهُ أَوْلَى بِالْعُذْرِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1042 - Ali ibn Mahziyar asked about this issue, and Imam (as) replied:\n\"He does not have to make up the fasting (sawm) or the prayers (salat), and everything that overwhelms a person due to God's will, God is more deserving of granting the excuse.\""
        ]
      }
